					<description><![CDATA[<p>See the biggest and best announcements from this year's Google Marketing Live event.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-marketing-live-2025">Google Marketing Live 2025: 10 Top Takeaways + Early Reactions</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>As expected, Google Marketing Live 2025 was an AI love fest. Eight presenters announced more than 30 new, almost exclusively AI tools and features to help marketers create, serve, and measure their ads.</p>
<p>We‚Äôll break down many of these announcements over the coming weeks, explaining how they work and what they mean for your success on Google Ads.</p>
<p>But for now, here‚Äôs a recap of the most important announcements from Google Marketing Live 2025, along with early reactions from PPC pros.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ol>
<li><a href="#expanded-ads-in-aios-and-ai-mode">Expanded ads in AIOs and AI Mode</a></li>
<li><a href="#power-pair-becomes-power-pack">Power Pair becomes Power Pack</a></li>
<li><a href="#ai-max-for-search-campaigns">AI Max for Search campaigns</a></li>
<li><a href="#channel-reporting-in-pmax">Channel reporting in PMax</a></li>
<li><a href="#smart-bidding-exploration-available-globally">Smart Bidding Exploration available globally</a></li>
<li><a href="#ai-agentic-tools-in-google-ads-and-google-analytics">AI agentic tools in Google Ads and Google Analytics</a></li>
<li><a href="#new-and-upgraded-measurement-tools">New and upgraded measurement tools</a></li>
<li><a href="#youtube-updates-for-ads-creators-and-conversions">YouTube updates for ads, creators, and conversions</a></li>
<li><a href="#ai-mode-shopping-experiences">AI Mode shopping experiences</a></li>
<li><a href="#marketing-advisor-coming-to-chrome-browsers">Marketing Advisor coming to Chrome browsers</a></li>
</ol>
<h2>10 biggest takeaways from Google Marketing Live 2025</h2>
<p>GML 2025 was a fast-paced presentation of the newest features in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/24/google-ads-examples">Google Ads</a>. Here are the biggest announcements from the event.</p>
<div id="expanded-ads-in-aios-and-ai-mode"></div>
<h3>1. Expanded ads in AIOs and AI Mode</h3>
<p>Several announcements highlighted Google‚Äôs push for AI-powered discovery. As the GML speakers put it, the goal is to turn non-commercial intent into ‚Äúads that don‚Äôt interrupt but help your customers discover you.‚Äù</p>
<p>Along that theme, users will soon begin to see expanded ads in their <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ai-overviews">AI Overviews</a> that align with the educational nature of the result. This is something we&#8217;ve anticipated since the announcement of AI Overviews.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs how it‚Äôll work. Say someone searches for ‚Äúhow to bring small dogs on flights,‚Äù they‚Äôll see an AIO with helpful tips and an ad for dog carriers.</p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-first.webp-1.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - AIO ads." width="793" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-91743 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-first.webp-1.webp 793w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-first.webp-1-480x363.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 793px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Likewise, users of Google Search&#8217;s newly released<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ai-mode"> AI Mode</a> will see ads that pull a commercial intent from an educational query and serve an ad to match it.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-ai-mode-mobile.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 -AI Mode ad on mobile." width="337" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-91744 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-ai-mode-mobile.webp 337w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-ai-mode-mobile-169x300.webp 169w" sizes="(max-width: 337px) 100vw, 337px" /></p>
<p>These new ad placements may be a big boon for advertisers hoping to engage customers as they use more complex search methods. But some PPC pros noted a glaring gap in the announcement: How will these new ads be tracked?</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-anu.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 -Tweet screenshot." width="601" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-91745 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-anu.webp 601w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-anu-480x479.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 601px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://x.com/TheMarketingAnu/status/1925544111869694451" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4aa.png" alt="üí™" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Are your Google Ads competitive with the rest of your industry?</strong> Get the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/google-ads-industry-benchmarks?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2025GoogleAdsBenchmarks_Download">2025 Google Ads Benchmarks Report</a> and find out.</p>
<div id="power-pair-becomes-power-pack"></div>
<h3>2. Power Pair becomes Power Pack</h3>
<p>Google announced the<a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/14835145?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Power Pair</a>‚Äîthe combo of AI-powered search campaigns and Performance Max‚Äîat GML 2024. This year, Google introduced its replacement, the Power Pack, which includes the trio of an upgraded<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/07/05/performance-max-tips"> Performance Max</a>, AI Max for Search campaigns, and Demand Gen.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-power-pack.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - Power Pack image." width="936" height="444" class="aligncenter wp-image-91746 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-power-pack.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-power-pack-480x228.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>A few of the new capabilities included in the Power Pack include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Channel performance reporting and higher granularity reporting in Performance Max (we‚Äôll cover this a little later).</li>
<li>New targeting and creative enhancements in AI Max for Search campaigns (detailed next!).</li>
<li>Upgraded <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/08/22/demand-gen-campaigns">Demand Gen campaigns</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>The sentiment among marketers on the new Power Pack was pretty positive. Several mentioned how useful its cross-platform integration will be. Overall, there seems to be a general acceptance that AI and Google Ads are inseparable.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/gml-2025-powerpack-ppcchat-tweet.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 -Tweet screenshot about power pack" width="900" height="693" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-91737" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/gml-2025-powerpack-ppcchat-tweet.webp 900w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/gml-2025-powerpack-ppcchat-tweet-480x370.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://x.com/JordanBanaf/status/1925230917385404620" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>However, to be fair, not every marketer is enamored with AI‚Äôs omnipresence.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-heather.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - Tweet screenshot about AI rollouts" width="841" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-91747 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-heather.webp 841w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-heather-480x342.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 841px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://x.com/HeatherMonahan_/status/1925236153592013061" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<div id="ai-max-for-search-campaigns"></div>
<h3>3. AI Max for Search campaigns</h3>
<p>AI Max for Search campaigns is a collection of<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-audience-targeting"> targeting</a> and creative tools designed to help you address the more complex ways people search for things online. You‚Äôll engage all AI Max tools with a single toggle.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-new-campaign.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - screenshot of Ad Manager." width="790" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-91748 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-new-campaign.webp 790w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-new-campaign-480x365.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 790px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>AI Max has two main feature sets to consider:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Asset optimization:</strong> AI Max for Search will use text from your existing ads, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/great-landing-pages">landing page</a> copy, and assets to adapt your headlines and descriptions on the fly and better meet the intent of a user‚Äôs query.</li>
<li><strong>Search term matching:</strong> Google AI learns from your current keywords, creatives, and URLs, then uses <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/broad-match">broad match</a> and keywordless technology to find higher-performing queries.</li>
</ul>
<p>AI Max for Search campaigns is due to roll out to all advertisers globally in beta by the end of May.</p>
<div id="channel-reporting-in-pmax"></div>
<h3>4. Channel reporting in PMax</h3>
<p>You‚Äôll soon see channel-level performance in your Performance Max campaigns.</p>
<p>Open your Channel performance page, and you‚Äôll see a new data visualization that illustrates which channels your customers are engaging on and how that‚Äôs affecting your conversion goals.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-channel.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - PMax channel chart." width="936" height="533" class="aligncenter wp-image-91749 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-channel.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-channel-480x273.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Improving attribution was a common theme during this year&#8217;s GML, which is a good step in that direction. The open beta for channel reporting in PMax will be available soon.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4b8.png" alt="üí∏" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Are you wasting money in Google Ads?</strong> Find out with our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader">Free Google Ads Performance Grader</a></p>
<div id="smart-bidding-exploration-available-globally"></div>
<h3>5. Smart Bidding Exploration available globally</h3>
<p>Smart Bidding Exploration, which is now available globally in beta, gives you a way to access some potentially lucrative<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2012/12/10/three-types-of-search-queries"> search queries</a> you may have missed out on before. It works by using machine learning to analyze a variety of signals and predicts how likely a conversion is for each<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/articles/what-is-google-adwords"> Google Ads auction</a>. It‚Äôll automatically adjust bids that may exceed ROAS targets but that are still within a targeted range.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-bidding.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - bidding screen." width="936" height="527" class="aligncenter wp-image-91750 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-bidding.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-bidding-480x270.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The flexibility of Smart Bidding Exploration offers less-rigid ROAS targets, which opens the door to new opportunities within existing campaigns.</p>
<div id="ai-agentic-tools-in-google-ads-and-google-analytics"></div>
<h3>6. AI agentic tools in Google Ads and Google Analytics</h3>
<p>Conversational AI is coming to your Google Ads and Google Analytics experience. These new AI agents will act like expert marketing guides that suggest and implement ways to optimize your campaigns. They‚Äôll learn from your performance and business data to generate reports, surface insights, and proactively find and fix<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/07/google-ads-mistakes"> problems in your Google Ads account</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-analytics.png" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 -Analytics AI." width="936" height="527" class="aligncenter wp-image-91720 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-analytics.png 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-analytics-480x270.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>This is one of the biggest leaps forward in how marketers learn from and manage their Google Ads campaigns. They‚Äôll make setup and execution much faster and improve ad targeting and performance if Google is right.</p>
<p>There were plenty of announcements about AI being used to create ads, too (like turning a static image into a full-on video). Some marketers noted the landmines that these tools lay out for compliance teams.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-kegan.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - Tweet screenshot." width="936" height="228" class="aligncenter wp-image-91752 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-kegan.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-kegan-480x117.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://x.com/JonKagan/status/1925235396545331569" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<div id="new-and-upgraded-measurement-tools"></div>
<h3>7. New and upgraded measurement tools</h3>
<p>Marketers constantly request more clarity for their ads, and Google answered at GML with several new and expanded analytics features.</p>
<p>The main measurement announcements at GML 2025 include:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>New Data Manager tools:</strong> Collect <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/04/12/first-party-data">first-party data</a> from more sources (like Salesforce, HubSpot, etc.), safely store it, and use it more effectively from a ‚Äúone-stop data shop.‚Äù</li>
<li><strong>Expanded incrementality testing:</strong> One of the biggest reactions from the live audience came when Google announced it had lowered the spend threshold on its incrementality testing to $5,000. That comes with an improved testing methodology for better outcomes.</li>
<li><strong>Cross-channel measurement enhancements:</strong> Google said deeper cross-channel insights are coming to Google Analytics, including impressions, across Google and other platforms like Reddit and Pinterest.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-data-manager.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - Data Manager." width="910" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-91753 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-data-manager.webp 910w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-data-manager-480x316.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 910px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>It‚Äôs no surprise that these updates took up a lot of the online chat oxygen after they were announced. The feedback was mostly cautiously optimistic, with an appreciation for new data sources but a call out for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/05/08/attribution-models">attribution</a> from social platforms.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/gml-2025-tweet-view-through-data-ga4.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - Tweet screenshot about view-through social data in GA4" width="900" height="282" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-91739" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/gml-2025-tweet-view-through-data-ga4.webp 900w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/gml-2025-tweet-view-through-data-ga4-480x150.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://x.com/SPoulton/status/1925297814189613435" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<div id="youtube-updates-for-ads-creators-and-conversions"></div>
<h3>8. YouTube updates for ads, creators, and conversions</h3>
<p>It seems video continues to be a bigger deal at Google. This year,<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/03/how-to-advertise-on-youtube"> YouTube advertising</a> took up much more space than in past GML events.</p>
<p>Three of the most significant YouTube announcements included:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Shoppable masthead:</strong> YouTube‚Äôs most prominent ad position is now open for interactive, shoppable ads on mobile.</li>
<li><strong>Accelerated checkout for Demand Gen YouTube ads:</strong> Redirect shoppers directly from in-stream ads to their cart or a checkout page on your website.</li>
<li><strong>YouTube creator partnership:</strong> Meet new creator partners, manage those relationships, and quickly integrate existing branded creator content into your ads.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-influencer.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - creator partnership screen." width="805" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-91754 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-influencer.webp 805w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-influencer-480x358.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 805px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>There was also an announcement about new ads on <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/youtube-shorts-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube Shorts</a>, which is a great addition for advertisers since Google says that 45% of Shorts users are not on TikTok. Put it all together, and it leads us to believe that video will be an even more important player in the upcoming year.</p>
<div id="ai-mode-shopping-experiences"></div>
<div id="ai-mode-shopping-experiences"></div>
<h3>9. AI Mode shopping experiences</h3>
<p>Beyond simply serving ads, Google announced that it‚Äôs pairing the power of Gemini with the vast collection of products in Shopping Graph to improve the online shopping experience in several ways.</p>
<p>First up, the presenters showed how <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/google-ai-mode/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI Mode can <strong>aid in product discovery</strong></a>. Say you have a light gray couch and search for a rug to pull the room together. AI Mode runs a bunch of simulated searches for you to learn which features fit your needs, then shows a panel of images and product listings. If you add new criteria, such as the rug needing to be water-resistant and durable, it‚Äôll dynamically update as you add those characteristics.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-ai-mode.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - AI mode shopping." width="828" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-91755 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-ai-mode.webp 828w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-ai-mode-480x348.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 828px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>There‚Äôs also a <strong>new price tracking feature</strong> in AI Mode. Once you‚Äôve picked the perfect rug, tap ‚Äútrack price‚Äù and set a buy price. The AI will notify you of price drops it finds, and when it hits your desired price, you can tap ‚Äúbuy for me,‚Äù and it‚Äôll complete the purchase using your Google Wallet.</p>
<p>Finally, AI Mode lets you virtually <strong>try on an outfit</strong>. Remember Cher‚Äôs closet app from Clueless? It‚Äôs like that. Upload a photo of yourself, and Google‚Äôs AI will generate a custom image of you wearing your new fit, even in different poses.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-try-on.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - try on screen." width="936" height="530" class="aligncenter wp-image-91756 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-try-on.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-try-on-480x272.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>GML tends to go heavy on innovations for physical product marketers. These new agentic shopping experiences will be particularly helpful to them.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/gml-2025-tweet-agentic-shopping.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 - Tweet screenshot about agentic shopping announcement" width="900" height="889" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-91740" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/gml-2025-tweet-agentic-shopping.webp 900w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/gml-2025-tweet-agentic-shopping-480x474.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://x.com/AndrewLolk/status/1925231829902405908" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<div id="marketing-advisor-coming-to-chrome-browsers"></div>
<h3>10. Marketing Advisor coming to Chrome browsers</h3>
<p>GML closed out with a live demo of an upcoming AI agent called Marketing Advisor that‚Äôll live right in your Chrome browser. The <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-agents">AI agent</a> will help advertisers manage all sorts of marketing tasks.</p>
<p>For example, Marketing Advisor may suggest product promotions based on seasonality. It can review your website and troubleshoot a<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/30/google-ads-conversion-tracking"> conversion tracking</a> problem. It could also assist with a big, multi-site tagging job, identifying where tags are needed and even adding them with permission.</p>
<p>Once rolled out, Google Advisor will appear as a Chrome browser side panel and operate like other familiar<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/chatbots"> conversational AI tools</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-summer-voyage.webp" alt="Google Marketing Live 2025 -Marketing Advisor screenshot." width="936" height="566" class="aligncenter wp-image-91757 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-summer-voyage.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-marketing-live-2025-wordstream-summer-voyage-480x290.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h2>Google Marketing Live 2025 covered a lot of ground</h2>
<p>GML 2025 lasted about 80 minutes. Take out the banter and video montages, and you‚Äôre left with less than an hour of actual product presentations. Still, the presenters crammed in a ton of announcements that‚Äôll affect every aspect of managing your Google Ads accounts.</p>
<p>As expected, the focus was squarely on AI and all the ways Google continues to integrate it in different ways to make managing, measuring, and tracking campaigns easier. Of course, time will tell if they actually move the needle for most advertisers.</p>
<p>There‚Äôs a LOT more to unpack from this year‚Äôs Google Marketing Live. We‚Äôll have advertising experts dig into several of the most impactful announcements and be here to help you understand what they mean for your business.</p>
