					<description><![CDATA[<p>Open AI just launched its own search experience: SearchGPT. Find out what this means for your business and how to prepare. </p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/chatgpt-search">SearchGPT: Everything You Should Know About the New ChatGPT Search</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>You‚Äôve probably heard of ChatGPT, the chatbot powered by artificial intelligence launched by OpenAI. You can ask ChatGPT a question, and machine learning will pump out a conversational response.</p>
<p>Now, <a href="https://openai.com/index/introducing-chatgpt-search/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenAI has announced</a> the roll-out of SearchGPT, a real-time web search feature within ChatGPT that offers live news and data from verified sources.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre marketing and advertising your business via search platforms like Google or Microsoft Bing, you might already have a few questions popping into your head like ‚Äúhow does SearchGPT work?‚Äù or ‚Äúhow will SearchGPT impact the paid and organic search spaces?‚Äù We‚Äôve got you covered with answers to all that and more in this complete SearchGPT breakdown.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#what-is-searchgpt">What is SearchGPT</a></li>
<li><a href="#chatgpt-search-pros-cons">What‚Äôs the big deal? Pros and cons of SearchGPT</a></li>
<li><a href="#chatgpt-search-comparison">How does SearchGPT compare to other search engines</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#chatgpt-search-versus-google">SearchGPT vs. Google</a></li>
<li><a href="#chatgpt-search-versus-bing">SearchGPT vs. Bing</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#how-to-prepare-for-chatgpt-search">How to prepare for ChatGPT search</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="what-is-searchgpt"></div>
<h2>What is SearchGPT?</h2>
<p>SearchGPT is an AI-powered search engine that turns answers to ChatGPT user queries into conversational responses based on real-time information from across the web‚Äîsimilar to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ai-overviews" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google‚Äôs AI Overviews</a>. Currently, only ChatGPT Plus and Team users can opt to try ChatGPT search, but there is a Chrome extension also available, and it will eventually roll out to all users.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-searchgpt-screenshot.webp" alt="chatgpt search - searchgpt option example screenshot" width="508" height="303" class="aligncenter wp-image-87137 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-searchgpt-screenshot.webp 508w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-searchgpt-screenshot-480x286.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 508px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://openai.com/index/introducing-chatgpt-search/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="üö®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>For more help navigating the rise of AI</strong>, download our free <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteAIinMarketingGuide.html?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_AIMarketing_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener">emergency guide to AI in marketing</a>!</p>
<div id="chatgpt-search-pros-cons"></div>
<h2>What‚Äôs the big deal? Pros and cons of SearchGPT</h2>
<p>Should you try using SearchGPT (when you get the chance)? Here are some of its pros and cons.</p>
<h3>Pros of SearchGPT</h3>
<p>SearchGPT can offer direct, concise, and relevant answers to questions rather than just providing a list of links like the traditional search experience. However, it also displays a sidebar with links to the original sources used to generate responses for fact-checking, and users can ask additional follow-up questions for a more interactive search experience.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-searchgpt-sources-example.webp" alt="chatgpt search - example of sources from searchgpt" width="859" height="501" class="aligncenter wp-image-87134 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-searchgpt-sources-example.webp 859w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-searchgpt-sources-example-480x280.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 859px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://openai.com/index/introducing-chatgpt-search/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<h3>Cons of SearchGPT</h3>
<p>We know that <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/28/ai-for-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI isn‚Äôt perfect</a>, and SearchGPT is no different. For example, the quality of SearchGPT responses is still going to depend on the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-prompts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI prompt</a> that the user inputs. So far, SearchGPT answers tend to be lengthy, so this solution may not make the cut for a quick, one-sentence answer to a question. Plus, like with any AI-powered output, you still need to fact-check the answers and sources provided to be absolutely sure you‚Äôre getting the right information.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f50d.png" alt="üîç" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Want ideas for new conversational queries your customers may be searching for?</strong> Try our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/keywords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Keywords_KWTool" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Free Keyword Tool</a>!</p>
<div id="chatgpt-search-comparison"></div>
<h2>How does SearchGPT compare to other search engines?</h2>
<p>If you‚Äôre wondering how SearchGPT differs from the typical search experience, here is how it compares to top search platforms such as Google and Microsoft.</p>
<div id="chatgpt-search-versus-google"></div>
<h3>SearchGPT versus Google</h3>
<p>So far, the <a href="https://searchengineland.com/searchgpt-what-you-need-to-know-446455" target="_blank" rel="noopener">search marketing and advertising community</a> has predicted that SearchGPT will <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-overviews-breaking-search" target="_blank" rel="noopener">outperform AI Overviews (AIO) on Google</a>. To start, SearchGPT is naturally much more conversational than AIO. It‚Äôs also more transparent in the sources it cites with the full sidebar display rather than the link icons <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ai-mode">Google uses in AIO</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-searchgpt-versus-google.webp" alt="chatgpt search - searchgpt versus google ai overviews example" width="818" height="375" class="aligncenter wp-image-87135 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-searchgpt-versus-google.webp 818w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-searchgpt-versus-google-480x220.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 818px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>When it comes to the traditional search experience, it&#8217;s too early to tell how SearchGPT can compare, especially when searching for local businesses or running ads. For now, we know that ChatGPT search currently has a somewhat <a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/chatgpt-search-vs-google-and-bing/531573/?user_id=%20&amp;utm_campaign=daily_newsletter_11_05_2024&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;_hsenc=p2ANqtz--YCY_CakIqri7PIxeIVA-T9Rl3mQjLEzvXRTvFggUb4PbHnCqXiO2CYfSz7-w8zcURg2nDLTYKeg_FNqpe2XJPQgl5AOCtMyiucgcYCx7DNPB3WLk&amp;_hsmi=332439008&amp;utm_source=sejtoday#placement_loop" target="_blank" rel="noopener">limited local search experience</a>, and it will actually direct you to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/google-maps-marketing-strategy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Maps</a> if you explicitly ask it for a result on a map.</p>
<div id="chatgpt-search-versus-bing"></div>
<h3>SearchGPT versus Bing</h3>
<p>Bing also has a conversational <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-agents">AI solution</a>, <a href="https://adoption.microsoft.com/en-us/copilot/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft Copilot</a>, which integrates with Bing search. One of the main differences is that Copilot does include some shopping features and capabilities, so unlike SearchGPT, users could make purchases directly from Bing‚Äôs AI search solution.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Understand how your customers might be searching for your business on SearchGPT and beyond </strong>using our free <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteTargetAudience.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_TargetAudineceGuide_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener">guide to finding (and marketing to) your target audience</a>!</p>
<div id="how-to-prepare-for-chatgpt-search"></div>
<h2>How to prepare for SearchGPT</h2>
<p>As more options for browsing the web, like SearchGPT, arise, be open to opportunities for your business to reach customers beyond traditional Google or Microsoft Bing searches. You may want to consider what types of key topics and questions your target market has, rather than solely focusing on transactional keywords.</p>
<p>As for ChatGPT search and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/ppc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PPC</a>, it&#8217;s too soon to know how it will treat ads or how SearchGPT will determine which content to display. <span data-teams="true"><span class="ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak" dir="ltr">OpenAI<a aria-label="Link has suggested" id="menurgu2" href="https://trueinteractive.com/blog/how-searchgpt-could-change-search-advertising/#:~:text=Though%20SearchGPT%20has%20not%20yet,traditional%20banners%20and%20sponsored%20links." rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank" class="fui-Link ___1q1shib f2hkw1w f3rmtva f1ewtqcl fyind8e f1k6fduh f1w7gpdv fk6fouc fjoy568 figsok6 f1s184ao f1mk8lai fnbmjn9 f1o700av f13mvf36 f1cmlufx f9n3di6 f1ids18y f1tx3yz7 f1deo86v f1eh06m1 f1iescvh fhgqx19 f1olyrje f1p93eir f1nev41a f1h8hb77 f1lqvz6u f10aw75t fsle3fq f17ae5zn" title="https://trueinteractive.com/blog/how-searchgpt-could-change-search-advertising/#:~:text=though%20searchgpt%20has%20not%20yet,traditional%20banners%20and%20sponsored%20links."> has suggested</a> that ads could become a part of the platform in the future, but instead of traditional text ads,<a aria-label="Link some sources expect" id="menurgu4" href="https://growthiqdigital.com/blog/searchgpt-ads-what-you-need-to-know/" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank" class="fui-Link ___1q1shib f2hkw1w f3rmtva f1ewtqcl fyind8e f1k6fduh f1w7gpdv fk6fouc fjoy568 figsok6 f1s184ao f1mk8lai fnbmjn9 f1o700av f13mvf36 f1cmlufx f9n3di6 f1ids18y f1tx3yz7 f1deo86v f1eh06m1 f1iescvh fhgqx19 f1olyrje f1p93eir f1nev41a f1h8hb77 f1lqvz6u f10aw75t fsle3fq f17ae5zn" title="https://growthiqdigital.com/blog/searchgpt-ads-what-you-need-to-know/"> some sources expect</a> there to be multimedia and conversational ads tailored to the user&#8217;s search journey.¬†</span></span></p>
<p>However, prioritizing user-friendly, helpful content and following best practices will likely set you up for success in the long term. SearchGPT seems to favor relevant, up-to-date, authoritative content that includes a variety of media beyond just text, like images and videos.</p>
<p>At the end of the day, no matter the platform, your website‚Äôs high-quality, engaging, and media-rich content will be at the top of your potential customer‚Äôs results.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-media-example.webp" alt="chatgpt search - searchgpt media rich results" width="885" height="457" class="aligncenter wp-image-87136 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-media-example.webp 885w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/chatgpt-search-media-example-480x248.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 885px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://searchengineland.com/searchgpt-what-you-need-to-know-446455" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<h2>Will ChatGPT search be a game-changer?</h2>
<p>Time will tell if SearchGPT is going to change the search landscape for the better or for the worse. While we wait on more to come, try being open to a variety of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/26/marketing-channels">marketing channels</a>, including ChatGPT search, to attract customers and optimize accordingly (even for <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/ai-for-small-business-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">small businesses</a>). For more help navigating major digital marketing landscape changes like this one, see how <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/marketing-services?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Demo_Blog_Demo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">our solutions</a> can help your business grow its search strategy.</p>
